							Margalit Fine












A 20-year veteran in the pharmaceutical and API industry, Margalit Fine joined AMRI in 2016. She has held multiple leadership positions at large-scale corporations, most recently as CEO of Euticals. Before joining Euticals, she held various roles at Teva, leading European API operations, which expanded its geographic footprint through the acquisition of several API businesses, and ultimately as chief procurement officer, where she drove initiatives to centralize Teva’s procurement activities. Ms. Fine has also served as the managing director and member of the board at Sicor. She received a bachelor’s degree in statistics as well as a master’s in operations research from Tel Aviv University.








